<br>
The mob you are pulling is a caster and in this case you can't get out of line of sight before HoS lands.  <br>
<br>
Without Bellow you pull with HoS and the mob gets a free nuke/root/debuff/etc before he'll follow you. (Yes, you could pull with mez and not have the mob cast on you but then you gotta wait for mez to wear off and is subject to resists)<br>
<br>
With Bellow you can still pull with HoS but toss bellow right after it hits to interrupt whatever spell the mob was gonna cast at you (and since you HoS'd, Bellow has a better chance of landing).  By the time it's casting time is done you are out of line of sight/range to the group.<br>
<br>
